# Integrating Claude into Next.js with Streaming

Here's the simplest approach using the Anthropic SDK with Next.js API routes:

## 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install @anthropic-ai/sdk
```

## 2. Create an API Route

**`pages/api/chat.ts`** (or `app/api/chat/route.ts` for App Router):

```typescript
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";

const client = new Anthropic();

export const runtime = "nodejs";

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages, context } = await req.json();

  const systemPrompt = `You are a helpful assistant answering questions about user data.
Here's the user's data context:
${context}`;

  const stream = client.messages.stream({
    model: "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022",
    max_tokens: 1024,
    system: systemPrompt,
    messages: messages,
  });

  return stream.toReadableStream();
}
```

## 3. Frontend Component

**`components/ChatInterface.tsx`**:

```typescript
"use client";
import { useState, useRef, useEffect } from "react";

export default function ChatInterface() {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<
    Array<{ role: "user" | "assistant"; content: string }>
  >([]);
  const [input, setInput] = useState("");
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (!input.trim()) return;

    const userMessage = input;
    setInput("");
    setMessages((prev) => [...prev, { role: "user", content: userMessage }]);
    setIsLoading(true);

    try {
      const response = await fetch("/api/chat", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          messages: [...messages, { role: "user", content: userMessage }],
          context: "Your user data here", // Pass relevant user data
        }),
      });

      if (!response.body) throw new Error("No response body");

      let assistantMessage = "";
      const reader = response.body.getReader();
      const decoder = new TextDecoder();

      // Process streaming response
      while (true) {
        const { done, value } = await reader.read();
        if (done) break;

        const chunk = decoder.decode(value);
        const lines = chunk.split("\n");

        for (const line of lines) {
          if (line.startsWith("data: ")) {
            try {
              const event = JSON.parse(line.slice(6));
              if (event.type === "content_block_delta") {
                assistantMessage += event.delta.text || "";
              }
            } catch {}
          }
        }
      }

      setMessages((prev) => [
        ...prev,
        { role: "assistant", content: assistantMessage },
      ]);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Error:", error);
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-screen">
      <div className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4">
        {messages.map((msg, i) => (
          <div key={i} className={`mb-4 ${msg.role === "user" ? "text-right" : ""}`}>
            <div
              className={`inline-block p-2 rounded ${
                msg.role === "user"
                  ? "bg-blue-500 text-white"
                  : "bg-gray-200 text-black"
              }`}
            >
              {msg.content}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="p-4 border-t">
        <input
          value={input}
          onChange={(e) => setInput(e.target.value)}
          placeholder="Ask about your data..."
          className="w-full p-2 border rounded"
          disabled={isLoading}
        />
      </form>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## 4. Environment Setup

**`.env.local`**:

```
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
```

## Key Features

- ✅ **Real-time streaming** - Users see responses appear word-by-word
- ✅ **Conversation history** - Messages persist in the chat
- ✅ **Context passing** - Include user data in the system prompt
- ✅ **Error handling** - Basic try/catch included
- ✅ **Works with both Pages and App Router**

## Optional Enhancements

**Better streaming UI** - Use a library like `react-use-streaming`:

```typescript
const { response, isLoading } = useStreamingResponse();
```

**Typesafety** - Define message types more strictly and add proper error types from the SDK.

**Token tracking** - Monitor usage for billing by checking response metadata.

This is production-ready for small to medium apps. For larger scale, consider adding request validation, rate limiting, and error tracking.

# Preventing Unnecessary Re-renders in React

Here are the best solutions, from simplest to most advanced:

## 1. **React.memo** (Functional Components)

Memoizes your component so it only re-renders if props actually change:

```jsx
const MyComponent = React.memo(({ name, age }) => {
  return <div>{name} - {age}</div>;
});
```

### With Custom Comparison

If default shallow comparison isn't enough:

```jsx
const MyComponent = React.memo(
  ({ data }) => <div>{data.value}</div>,
  (prevProps, nextProps) => {
    return prevProps.data.value === nextProps.data.value; // true = skip re-render
  }
);
```

## 2. **useMemo** (For Expensive Calculations)

Memoize values passed as props to prevent child re-renders:

```jsx
function Parent() {
  const memoizedData = useMemo(() => ({ id: 1, name: 'John' }), []);

  return <Child data={memoizedData} />;
}
```

## 3. **useCallback** (For Function Props)

Prevent function references from changing on every render:

```jsx
function Parent() {
  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    console.log('Clicked');
  }, []); // Only recreated if dependencies change

  return <Child onClick={handleClick} />;
}
```

## 4. **PureComponent** (Class Components)

```jsx
class MyComponent extends React.PureComponent {
  render() {
    return <div>{this.props.name}</div>;
  }
}
```

---

## ⚠️ Common Pitfall

**Don't do this** - it defeats memoization:

```jsx
// ❌ Bad: New object created every render
<Child data={{ id: 1 }} />

// ✅ Good: Memoize the object
const data = useMemo(() => ({ id: 1 }), []);
<Child data={data} />
```

## Quick Decision Tree

- **Simple case (props rarely change)** → `React.memo`
- **Props are objects/arrays** → `useMemo` + `React.memo`
- **Passing functions as props** → `useCallback` + `React.memo`
- **Complex comparison logic** → `React.memo` with custom comparator
- **Class components** → `PureComponent`

Which scenario matches your use case?

# Simplest Integration for Next.js + Claude Streaming

For real-time streaming responses about user data in a Next.js app, here's the minimal setup:

## 1. **API Route + Messages API (Simplest Path)**

Create a Next.js API route that streams Claude responses directly to the client:

```typescript
// app/api/chat/route.ts
import Anthropic from "@anthropic-ai/sdk";

const client = new Anthropic();

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { message, context } = await req.json();

  const stream = await client.messages.stream({
    model: "claude-opus-4.6",
    max_tokens: 1024,
    system: `You are a helpful assistant analyzing user data. 
      Context: ${context}`,
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: message }],
  });

  // Return ReadableStream for Next.js streaming
  return new Response(stream.toReadableStream(), {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "text/event-stream" },
  });
}
```

```typescript
// components/ChatInput.tsx
"use client";
import { useState } from "react";

export default function ChatInput() {
  const [response, setResponse] = useState("");

  const handleAsk = async (question: string) => {
    const res = await fetch("/api/chat", {
      method: "POST",
      body: JSON.stringify({
        message: question,
        context: "User's relevant data here",
      }),
    });

    const reader = res.body?.getReader();
    const decoder = new TextDecoder();

    while (true) {
      const { done, value } = await reader!.read();
      if (done) break;

      const text = decoder.decode(value);
      setResponse((prev) => prev + text);
    }
  };

  return (
    <>
      <input
        onKeyDown={(e) =>
          e.key === "Enter" && handleAsk(e.currentTarget.value)
        }
      />
      <div>{response}</div>
    </>
  );
}
```

**Why this first:**
- ✅ No extra dependencies (just `@anthropic-ai/sdk`)
- ✅ Real-time streaming out of the box
- ✅ Handles auth server-side (API key stays secure)
- ✅ Works with any amount of user data you pass in the system prompt

---

## 2. **For Multi-Turn Conversations (Next Step)**

If users need to ask follow-up questions and build context:

```typescript
// app/api/chat/route.ts
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages, context } = await req.json();
  // messages is an array of {role, content} objects from client

  const stream = await client.messages.stream({
    model: "claude-opus-4.6",
    max_tokens: 1024,
    system: `You are analyzing user data.\nContext: ${context}`,
    messages: messages, // Pass full conversation history
  });

  return new Response(stream.toReadableStream(), {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "text/event-stream" },
  });
}
```

Then maintain message history client-side:
```typescript
const [messages, setMessages] = useState([]);

const handleAsk = async (question: string) => {
  const newMessages = [...messages, { role: "user", content: question }];
  setMessages(newMessages);

  const res = await fetch("/api/chat", {
    method: "POST",
    body: JSON.stringify({ messages: newMessages, context }),
  });
  // Stream and append assistant response...
};
```

---

## 3. **When to Consider More Advanced Patterns**

Only if you hit these constraints:

| Scenario | Recommendation |
|----------|-----------------|
| **Users query very large datasets** (>100K tokens) | Use 1M context (beta) + Files API to avoid re-uploading |
| **You want to avoid stream processing on client** | Use Agent SDK instead — Claude handles the tool loop server-side |
| **Data lives in a database/API** | Add MCP server to let Claude query it directly at runtime |
| **Users need sub-second latency on simple tasks** | Tier models: Haiku for initial filtering, Sonnet for final answer |

---

## 4. **Quick Checklist**

- [ ] Install SDK: `npm install @anthropic-ai/sdk`
- [ ] Set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` in `.env.local`
- [ ] Create `/api/chat` route (code above)
- [ ] Build streaming client (fetch + ReadableStream loop)
- [ ] Test with a simple question first

**Total lines of code to start: ~30.**

